\'91I\'92ll pull off his cassock,\'92 she says. You can\'92t think how she keeps\
begging me to bring you. I wondered why she took such an interest in you.\
Do you know, she\'92s an extraordinary woman, too!\'94\
\
\'93Thank her and say I\'92m not coming,\'94 said Alyosha, with a strained smile.\
\'93Finish what you were saying, Misha. I\'92ll tell you my idea after.\'94\
\
\'93There\'92s nothing to finish. It\'92s all clear. It\'92s the same old tune,\
brother. If even you are a sensualist at heart, what of your brother,\
Ivan? He\'92s a Karamazov, too. What is at the root of all you Karamazovs is\
