come into collision, the precious father and son, on that path! But\
Grushenka favors neither of them, she\'92s still playing with them, and\
teasing them both, considering which she can get most out of. For though\
she could filch a lot of money from the papa he wouldn\'92t marry her, and\
maybe he\'92ll turn stingy in the end, and keep his purse shut. That\'92s where\
Mitya\'92s value comes in; he has no money, but he\'92s ready to marry her. Yes,\
ready to marry her! to abandon his betrothed, a rare beauty, Katerina\
Ivanovna, who\'92s rich, and the daughter of a colonel, and to marry\
Grushenka, who has been the mistress of a dissolute old merchant,\
Samsonov, a coarse, uneducated, provincial mayor. Some murderous conflict\
