\'93Smerdyakov always pokes himself in now, after dinner. It\'92s you he\'92s so\
interested in. What have you done to fascinate him?\'94 he added to Ivan.\
\
\'93Nothing whatever,\'94 answered Ivan. \'93He\'92s pleased to have a high opinion of\
me; he\'92s a lackey and a mean soul. Raw material for revolution, however,\
