\
\'93He\'92s storing up ideas,\'94 said Ivan, smiling.\
\
\'93You see, I know he can\'92t bear me, nor any one else, even you, though you\
fancy that he has a high opinion of you. Worse still with Alyosha, he\
despises Alyosha. But he doesn\'92t steal, that\'92s one thing, and he\'92s not a\
gossip, he holds his tongue, and doesn\'92t wash our dirty linen in public.\
