to come to me. Do you understand what I want from you? Now, tell me\
simply, tell me every word of the message he sent you with (I knew he\
would send you).\'94\
\
\'93He told me to give you his compliments\'97and to say that he would never\
come again\'97but to give you his compliments.\'94\
\
\'93His compliments? Was that what he said\'97his own expression?\'94\
\
\'93Yes.\'94\
\
\'93Accidentally perhaps he made a mistake in the word, perhaps he did not\
use the right word?\'94\
\
\'93No; he told me precisely to repeat that word. He begged me two or three\
times not to forget to say so.\'94\
\
Katerina Ivanovna flushed hotly.\
\
\'93Help me now, Alexey Fyodorovitch. Now I really need your help. I\'92ll tell\
you what I think, and you must simply say whether it\'92s right or not.\
