\
This was unmistakably said with some malice and obviously with intention;\
even perhaps with no desire to conceal that he spoke ironically and with\
intention.\
\
\'93Oh, dear, how mistaken it all is!\'94 Madame Hohlakov cried again.\
\
\'93Alexey Fyodorovitch, you speak. I want dreadfully to know what you will\
say!\'94 cried Katerina Ivanovna, and burst into tears. Alyosha got up from\
the sofa.\
\
\'93It\'92s nothing, nothing!\'94 she went on through her tears. \'93I\'92m upset, I\
didn\'92t sleep last night. But by the side of two such friends as you and\
