But what\'92s the matter?\'94\
\
\'93I couldn\'92t have believed it. I can\'92t understand it!\'94 Alyosha cried\
suddenly in distress.\
\
\'93What? What?\'94\
\
\'93He is going to Moscow, and you cry out that you are glad. You said that\
on purpose! And you begin explaining that you are not glad of that but\
sorry to be\'97losing a friend. But that was acting, too\'97you were playing a\
