by!\'94\
\
She turned and disappeared behind the porti\'e8re so quickly that Alyosha had\
not time to utter a word, though he wanted to speak. He longed to beg her\
pardon, to blame himself, to say something, for his heart was full and he\
could not bear to go out of the room without it. But Madame Hohlakov took\
him by the hand and drew him along with her. In the hall she stopped him\
again as before.\
\
\'93She is proud, she is struggling with herself; but kind, charming,\
generous,\'94 she exclaimed, in a half\uc0\u8208 whisper. \'93Oh, how I love her,\
especially sometimes, and how glad I am again of everything! Dear Alexey\
Fyodorovitch, you didn\'92t know, but I must tell you, that we all, all\'97both\
her aunts, I and all of us, Lise, even\'97have been hoping and praying for\
