\
\'93But she has been crying\'97she has been wounded again,\'94 cried Alyosha.\
\
\'93Never trust a woman\'92s tears, Alexey Fyodorovitch. I am never for the\
women in such cases. I am always on the side of the men.\'94\
\
\'93Mamma, you are spoiling him,\'94 Lise\'92s little voice cried from behind the\
door.\
\
\'93No, it was all my fault. I am horribly to blame,\'94 Alyosha repeated\
unconsoled, hiding his face in his hands in an agony of remorse for his\
