\
\'93Quite the contrary; you behaved like an angel, like an angel. I am ready\
to say so a thousand times over.\'94\
\
\'93Mamma, how has he behaved like an angel?\'94 Lise\'92s voice was heard again.\
\
\'93I somehow fancied all at once,\'94 Alyosha went on as though he had not\
heard Lise, \'93that she loved Ivan, and so I said that stupid thing.... What\
will happen now?\'94\
\
\'93To whom, to whom?\'94 cried Lise. \'93Mamma, you really want to be the death of\
me. I ask you and you don\'92t answer.\'94\
\
At the moment the maid ran in.\
\
\'93Katerina Ivanovna is ill.... She is crying, struggling ... hysterics.\'94\
\
\'93What is the matter?\'94 cried Lise, in a tone of real anxiety. \'93Mamma, I\
shall be having hysterics, and not she!\'94\
\
\'93Lise, for mercy\'92s sake, don\'92t scream, don\'92t persecute me. At your age one\
can\'92t know everything that grown\uc0\u8208 up people know. I\'92ll come and tell you\
everything you ought to know. Oh, mercy on us! I am coming, I am\
coming.... Hysterics is a good sign, Alexey Fyodorovitch; it\'92s an\
