asked, \'91are the rich people stronger than any one else on earth?\'92 \'91Yes,\
Ilusha,\'92 I said, \'91there are no people on earth stronger than the rich.\'92\
\'91Father,\'92 he said, \'91I will get rich, I will become an officer and conquer\
everybody. The Tsar will reward me, I will come back here and then no one\
will dare\'97\'92 Then he was silent and his lips still kept trembling.\
\'91Father,\'92 he said, \'91what a horrid town this is.\'92 \'91Yes, Ilusha,\'92 I said,\
\'91it isn\'92t a very nice town.\'92 \'91Father, let us move into another town, a\
nice one,\'92 he said, \'91where people don\'92t know about us.\'92 \'91We will move, we\
will, Ilusha,\'92 said I, \'91only I must save up for it.\'92 I was glad to be able\
to turn his mind from painful thoughts, and we began to dream of how we\
would move to another town, how we would buy a horse and cart. \'91We will\
