\
\'93Yes, Lise, I have a secret one, too,\'94 answered Alyosha mournfully. \'93I see\
you love me, since you guessed that.\'94\
\
\'93What grief? What about? Can you tell me?\'94 asked Lise with timid entreaty.\
\
\'93I\'92ll tell you later, Lise\'97afterwards,\'94 said Alyosha, confused. \'93Now you\
wouldn\'92t understand it perhaps\'97and perhaps I couldn\'92t explain it.\'94\
\
\'93I know your brothers and your father are worrying you, too.\'94\
\
\'93Yes, my brothers too,\'94 murmured Alyosha, pondering.\
\
\'93I don\'92t like your brother Ivan, Alyosha,\'94 said Lise suddenly.\
\
He noticed this remark with some surprise, but did not answer it.\
\
\'93My brothers are destroying themselves,\'94 he went on, \'93my father, too. And\
they are destroying others with them. It\'92s \'91the primitive force of the\
