\
\'93Only don\'92t tell her that,\'94 said Alyosha, \'93or she will be upset, and\
that\'92s bad for her now.\'94\
\
\'93Sensible advice from a sensible young man. Am I to understand that you\
only agreed with her from compassion for her invalid state, because you\
didn\'92t want to irritate her by contradiction?\'94\
\
\'93Oh, no, not at all. I was quite serious in what I said,\'94 Alyosha declared\
stoutly.\
\
\'93To be serious about it is impossible, unthinkable, and in the first place\
I shall never be at home to you again, and I shall take her away, you may\
be sure of that.\'94\
\
\'93But why?\'94 asked Alyosha. \'93It\'92s all so far off. We may have to wait\
another year and a half.\'94\
\
\'93Ah, Alexey Fyodorovitch, that\'92s true, of course, and you\'92ll have time to\
