\
\'93No, there\'92s no need. Tell me, how is Katerina Ivanovna now? I must know.\'94\
\
\'93She still lies in delirium; she has not regained consciousness. Her aunts\
are here; but they do nothing but sigh and give themselves airs.\
Herzenstube came, and he was so alarmed that I didn\'92t know what to do for\
him. I nearly sent for a doctor to look after him. He was driven home in\
my carriage. And on the top of it all, you and this letter! It\'92s true\
nothing can happen for a year and a half. In the name of all that\'92s holy,\
