say nothing of the sufferings of grown\uc0\u8208 up people, they have eaten the\
apple, damn them, and the devil take them all! But these little ones! I am\
making you suffer, Alyosha, you are not yourself. I\'92ll leave off if you\
like.\'94\
\
\'93Never mind. I want to suffer too,\'94 muttered Alyosha.\
\
\'93One picture, only one more, because it\'92s so curious, so characteristic,\
and I have only just read it in some collection of Russian antiquities.\
I\'92ve forgotten the name. I must look it up. It was in the darkest days of\
