\
\'93But allow me, too!\'94 Mitya cried suddenly. \'93For the last time I entreat\
you, tell me, can I have the sum you promised me to\uc0\u8208 day, if not, when may\
I come for it?\'94\
\
\'93What sum, Dmitri Fyodorovitch?\'94\
\
\'93The three thousand you promised me ... that you so generously\'97\'94\
\
\'93Three thousand? Roubles? Oh, no, I haven\'92t got three thousand,\'94 Madame\
Hohlakov announced with serene amazement. Mitya was stupefied.\
\
\'93Why, you said just now ... you said ... you said it was as good as in my\
hands\'97\'94\
\
\'93Oh, no, you misunderstood me, Dmitri Fyodorovitch. In that case you\
