\
\'93I will certainly speak to some one, I\'92ll go at once,\'94 said Pyotr Ilyitch,\
after reading the paper.\
\
\'93You won\'92t have time, dear boy, come and have a drink. March!\'94\
\
Plotnikov\'92s shop was at the corner of the street, next door but one to\
Pyotr Ilyitch\'92s. It was the largest grocery shop in our town, and by no\
means a bad one, belonging to some rich merchants. They kept everything\
