was the utmost she had allowed him.\'94\
\
By the time Mitya and Pyotr Ilyitch reached the shop, they found a cart\
with three horses harnessed abreast with bells, and with Andrey, the\
driver, ready waiting for Mitya at the entrance. In the shop they had\
almost entirely finished packing one box of provisions, and were only\
waiting for Mitya\'92s arrival to nail it down and put it in the cart. Pyotr\
Ilyitch was astounded.\
\
\'93Where did this cart come from in such a hurry?\'94 he asked Mitya.\
\
\'93I met Andrey as I ran to you, and told him to drive straight here to the\
shop. There\'92s no time to lose. Last time I drove with Timofey, but Timofey\
