\
\'93Tut\'97tut\'97tut! That\'92s it, is it? So you\'92re off there to make trouble!\'94\
muttered Pyotr Ilyitch. \'93Now, it\'92s all clear, as clear as daylight. Dmitri\
Fyodorovitch, give me your pistols at once if you mean to behave like a\
man,\'94 he shouted aloud to Mitya. \'93Do you hear, Dmitri?\'94\
\
\'93The pistols? Wait a bit, brother, I\'92ll throw them into the pool on the\
road,\'94 answered Mitya. \'93Fenya, get up, don\'92t kneel to me. Mitya won\'92t hurt\
any one, the silly fool won\'92t hurt any one again. But I say, Fenya,\'94 he\
shouted, after having taken his seat. \'93I hurt you just now, so forgive me\
