\
\'93Why I needed it?... Oh, for one thing and another.... Well, it was to pay\
a debt.\'94\
\
\'93A debt to whom?\'94\
\
\'93That I absolutely refuse to answer, gentlemen. Not because I couldn\'92t, or\
because I shouldn\'92t dare, or because it would be damaging, for it\'92s all a\
paltry matter and absolutely trifling, but\'97I won\'92t, because it\'92s a matter\
