would stay there till midnight.\
\
\'93If I didn\'92t kill Fenya then, gentlemen, it was only because I hadn\'92t\
time,\'94 broke from him suddenly at that point in his story. That, too, was\
carefully written down. Mitya waited gloomily, and was beginning to tell\
