won\'92t tell you any more.\'94\
\
He sat with his elbows on the table and his head in his hand. He sat\
sideways to them and gazed at the wall, struggling against a feeling of\
nausea. He had, in fact, an awful inclination to get up and declare that\
he wouldn\'92t say another word, \'93not if you hang me for it.\'94\
\
\'93You see, gentlemen,\'94 he said at last, with difficulty controlling\
himself, \'93you see. I listen to you and am haunted by a dream.... It\'92s a\
dream I have sometimes, you know.... I often dream it\'97it\'92s always the same\
... that some one is hunting me, some one I\'92m awfully afraid of ... that\
he\'92s hunting me in the dark, in the night ... tracking me, and I hide\
