That\'92s just what you\'92re doing now. It\'92s just like that!\'94\
\
\'93Is that the sort of thing you dream about?\'94 inquired the prosecutor.\
\
\'93Yes, it is. Don\'92t you want to write it down?\'94 said Mitya, with a\
distorted smile.\
\
\'93No; no need to write it down. But still you do have curious dreams.\'94\
\
\'93It\'92s not a question of dreams now, gentlemen\'97this is realism, this is\
real life! I\'92m a wolf and you\'92re the hunters. Well, hunt him down!\'94\
\
\'93You are wrong to make such comparisons ...\'94 began Nikolay Parfenovitch,\
with extraordinary softness.\
\
\'93No, I\'92m not wrong, not at all!\'94 Mitya flared up again, though his\
