for by Katerina Ivanovna, formerly my betrothed. Do you know her?\'94\
\
\'93Yes, of course.\'94\
\
\'93I know you know her. She\'92s a noble creature, noblest of the noble. But\
she has hated me ever so long, oh, ever so long ... and hated me with good\
reason, good reason!\'94\
\
\'93Katerina Ivanovna!\'94 Nikolay Parfenovitch exclaimed with wonder. The\
prosecutor, too, stared.\
\
\'93Oh, don\'92t take her name in vain! I\'92m a scoundrel to bring her into it.\
Yes, I\'92ve seen that she hated me ... a long while.... From the very first,\
even that evening at my lodging ... but enough, enough. You\'92re unworthy\
even to know of that. No need of that at all.... I need only tell you that\
