\
\'93It\'92s the babe,\'94 answered the driver, \'93the babe weeping.\'94\
\
And Mitya was struck by his saying, in his peasant way, \'93the babe,\'94 and he\
liked the peasant\'92s calling it a \'93babe.\'94 There seemed more pity in it.\
\
\'93But why is it weeping?\'94 Mitya persisted stupidly, \'93why are its little\
arms bare? Why don\'92t they wrap it up?\'94\
\
\'93The babe\'92s cold, its little clothes are frozen and don\'92t warm it.\'94\
\
\'93But why is it? Why?\'94 foolish Mitya still persisted.\
\
\'93Why, they\'92re poor people, burnt out. They\'92ve no bread. They\'92re begging\
because they\'92ve been burnt out.\'94\
\
\'93No, no,\'94 Mitya, as it were, still did not understand. \'93Tell me why it is\
