\
Chapter IX. They Carry Mitya Away\
\
\
When the protocol had been signed, Nikolay Parfenovitch turned solemnly to\
the prisoner and read him the \'93Committal,\'94 setting forth, that in such a\
year, on such a day, in such a place, the investigating lawyer of such\uc0\u8208 \
and\uc0\u8208 such a district court, having examined so\u8208 and\u8208 so (to wit, Mitya)\
accused of this and of that (all the charges were carefully written out)\
and having considered that the accused, not pleading guilty to the charges\
made against him, had brought forward nothing in his defense, while the\
witnesses, so\uc0\u8208 and\u8208 so, and so\u8208 and\u8208 so, and the circumstances such\u8208 and\u8208 such\
testify against him, acting in accordance with such\uc0\u8208 and\u8208 such articles of\
the Statute Book, and so on, has ruled, that, in order to preclude so\uc0\u8208 and\u8208 \
so (Mitya) from all means of evading pursuit and judgment he be detained\
in such\uc0\u8208 and\u8208 such a prison, which he hereby notifies to the accused and\
