the market women with a silly stare.\
\
The women laughed.\
\
\'93You can never tell what he\'92s after,\'94 said one of them.\
\
\'93What Sabaneyev is it he\'92s talking about?\'94 the young man repeated, still\
furious and brandishing his right arm.\
\
\'93It must be a Sabaneyev who worked for the Kuzmitchovs, that\'92s who it must\
be,\'94 one of the women suggested.\
\
The young man stared at her wildly.\
\
\'93For the Kuzmitchovs?\'94 repeated another woman. \'93But his name wasn\'92t\
Trifon. His name\'92s Kuzma, not Trifon; but the boy said Trifon Nikititch,\
