\
\'93Let him alone, Kolya. Let\'92s go on.\'94\
\
\'93Nothing could stop me, now I am once off. Hey, good morning, peasant!\'94\
\
A sturdy\uc0\u8208 looking peasant, with a round, simple face and grizzled beard,\
who was walking by, raised his head and looked at the boy. He seemed not\
quite sober.\
\
\'93Good morning, if you are not laughing at me,\'94 he said deliberately in\
reply.\
\
\'93And if I am?\'94 laughed Kolya.\
\
\'93Well, a joke\'92s a joke. Laugh away. I don\'92t mind. There\'92s no harm in a\
joke.\'94\
\
\'93I beg your pardon, brother, it was a joke.\'94\
\
\'93Well, God forgive you!\'94\
\
\'93Do you forgive me, too?\'94\
\
\'93I quite forgive you. Go along.\'94\
\
\'93I say, you seem a clever peasant.\'94\
\
\'93Cleverer than you,\'94 the peasant answered unexpectedly, with the same\
