\
\'93I doubt it,\'94 said Kolya, somewhat taken aback.\
\
\'93It\'92s true, though.\'94\
\
\'93Perhaps it is.\'94\
\
\'93It is, brother.\'94\
\
\'93Good\uc0\u8208 by, peasant!\'94\
\
\'93Good\uc0\u8208 by!\'94\
\
\'93There are all sorts of peasants,\'94 Kolya observed to Smurov after a brief\
silence. \'93How could I tell I had hit on a clever one? I am always ready to\
