\
\'93Why, who taught you all this?\'94 cried Alyosha, surprised at last.\
\
\'93In the first place I am capable of thinking for myself without being\
taught. Besides, what I said just now about the classics being translated\
our teacher Kolbasnikov has said to the whole of the third class.\'94\
\
\'93The doctor has come!\'94 cried Nina, who had been silent till then.\
\
A carriage belonging to Madame Hohlakov drove up to the gate. The captain,\
