\
\'93Well? Did you talk to him?\'94 Grushenka put in eagerly.\
\
\'93He listened and said nothing. He told me that he had already formed his\
opinion. But he promised to give my words consideration.\'94\
\
\'93Consideration! Ah, they are swindlers! They\'92ll ruin him. And why did she\
send for the doctor?\'94\
\
\'93As an expert. They want to prove that Mitya\'92s mad and committed the\
