\
\'93Yes; but that would be the truth if he had killed him!\'94 cried Grushenka.\
\'93He was mad then, perfectly mad, and that was my fault, wretch that I am!\
But, of course, he didn\'92t do it, he didn\'92t do it! And they are all against\
him, the whole town. Even Fenya\'92s evidence went to prove he had done it.\
And the people at the shop, and that official, and at the tavern, too,\
before, people had heard him say so! They are all, all against him, all\
crying out against him.\'94\
\
\'93Yes, there\'92s a fearful accumulation of evidence,\'94 Alyosha observed\
