without her I can\'92t exist....\'94\
\
Mitya walked frowning across the room. It was almost dark. He suddenly\
seemed terribly worried.\
\
\'93So there\'92s a secret, she says, a secret? We have got up a plot against\
her, and Katya is mixed up in it, she thinks. No, my good Grushenka,\
that\'92s not it. You are very wide of the mark, in your foolish feminine\
