could reach the ears of the soldiers on guard.\
\
\'93I will tell you all our secret,\'94 Mitya whispered hurriedly. \'93I meant to\
tell you later, for how could I decide on anything without you? You are\
everything to me. Though I say that Ivan is superior to us, you are my\
angel. It\'92s your decision will decide it. Perhaps it\'92s you that is\
superior and not Ivan. You see, it\'92s a question of conscience, question of\
