peu de peine!_\'92 Fancy, such an answer! I drew back. It was the cry of\
nature, better than innocence itself, if you like. I absolved her sin on\
the spot and was turning to go, but I was forced to turn back. I heard the\
priest at the grating making an appointment with her for the\
evening\'97though he was an old man hard as flint, he fell in an instant! It\
was nature, the truth of nature asserted its rights! What, you are turning\
up your nose again? Angry again? I don\'92t know how to please you\'97\'94\
\
\'93Leave me alone, you are beating on my brain like a haunting nightmare,\'94\
Ivan moaned miserably, helpless before his apparition. \'93I am bored with\
you, agonizingly and insufferably. I would give anything to be able to\
shake you off!\'94\
