\
The visitor talked, obviously carried away by his own eloquence, speaking\
louder and louder and looking ironically at his host. But he did not\
succeed in finishing; Ivan suddenly snatched a glass from the table and\
flung it at the orator.\
\
\'93_Ah, mais c\'92est b\'eate enfin_,\'94 cried the latter, jumping up from the sofa\
and shaking the drops of tea off himself. \'93He remembers Luther\'92s inkstand!\
He takes me for a dream and throws glasses at a dream! It\'92s like a woman!\
I suspected you were only pretending to stop up your ears.\'94\
\
A loud, persistent knocking was suddenly heard at the window. Ivan jumped\
up from the sofa.\
\
\'93Do you hear? You\'92d better open,\'94 cried the visitor; \'93it\'92s your brother\
Alyosha with the most interesting and surprising news, I\'92ll be bound!\'94\
\
\'93Be silent, deceiver, I knew it was Alyosha, I felt he was coming, and of\
