\
\'93Stay\'94\'97he got up from the sofa\'97\'93an hour ago I took that new towel from\
there and wetted it. I wrapped it round my head and threw it down here ...\
How is it it\'92s dry? There was no other.\'94\
\
\'93You put that towel on your head?\'94 asked Alyosha.\
\
\'93Yes, and walked up and down the room an hour ago ... Why have the candles\
burnt down so? What\'92s the time?\'94\
\
\'93Nearly twelve.\'94\
\
\'93No, no, no!\'94 Ivan cried suddenly. \'93It was not a dream. He was here; he\
was sitting here, on that sofa. When you knocked at the window, I threw a\
glass at him ... this one. Wait a minute. I was asleep last time, but this\
